# ROVEXO Master UI Specification Mode (v1.0)

**STATUS: MANDATORY | PLATFORM-WIDE | FROM NOW ON**

Do **not** implement or redesign UI from screenshots alone.
Screenshots are visual reference only. Implementation follows an approved Master UI Spec.

## Gate

1. Write Master UI Spec (`docs/modules/<module>/MASTER_UI_SPECIFICATION.md`)
2. Include all 10 deliverables (see template)
3. Wait for explicit human approval
4. Only then implement — 1:1 to the spec
5. Freeze only after visual QA vs spec + mockup

## Forbidden without approved spec

- Estimating spacing, type, radius, shadows, colours, or sizes
- Separate Mobile / Desktop / Tablet components or layouts
- Desktop redesigns, dark alternate card themes, hierarchy changes
- “Close enough” screenshot matching

## Canonical UI rules

- **One** page component, **one** design, **one** source of truth
- Desktop / tablet / PWA may change **only**: max-width, grid columns, horizontal spacing
- Everything else identical across breakpoints

## Required deliverables (every page)

1. Master UI Specification  
2. Component Dimension Table  
3. Spacing Table  
4. Typography Table  
5. Colour Table  
6. Interaction Specification  
7. Responsive Specification  
8. Accessibility Specification  
9. Developer Notes  
10. QA Checklist  

Template: `docs/engineering/MASTER_UI_SPECIFICATION_TEMPLATE.md`

## Component fields (mandatory)

For every component: Name, Purpose, X/Y, Width, Height, Padding, Margin, Gap, Radius, Shadow, Background, Border, Icon, Icon Size, Icon Stroke, Title/Body fonts, Weight, Size, Line Height, Letter Spacing, Alignment, Pressed/Hover/Focus/Disabled/Loading/Empty, Animation, Navigation, Responsive Behaviour.

## Wallet

Wallet v1.0 is **not frozen**. Further Wallet visual work requires an approved Wallet Master UI Spec first.
